On Saturday, April 9 at 5.15pm the main Grand National race will be underway at Merseyside’s famous Aintree racecourse. it’s the 174th time the race has been run, and is the biggest horse racing event of the year – even inspiring those who don’t usually spectate to watch live on TV or place a bet. And there’s a lot in it for the owners, trainers and jockeys – as the winning horse takes the lion’s share of a jaw-dropping prize fund. But which runners will be up this year, and who’ll be riding them? Here’s the line-up for the 2022 Grand National – including the trainer, jockey and the rating they’ve been given out of 10. MORE : When is the Grand National 2022? How to watch and full race schedule MORE : How many horses have died at the Grand National? MORE : Bryony Frost claims fellow jockey Robbie Dunne ‘opened towel up and shook himself’ in changing room Follow Metro across our social channels, on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram Share your views in the comments below 